  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you attempt to learn or recall a historical or scientific fact, if you don't know that information, you know where and from whom you can obtain it.</p><p>Knowing where the information can be found doesn't automatically enable you to learn it; you might need to offer bribes, favors, or other incentives to induce people to reveal their secrets.</p><p>Your DM might rule that the knowledge you seek is secreted away in an inaccessible place, or that it simply can't be found.</p><p>Unearthing the deepest secrets of the land can require an adventure or even a whole campaign.</p>",
